      "uuid": "019b1b81-3b95-719e-a005-7ae00b838154",
      "text": "The user is saying \"hey Luna\" which triggers the Luna Activation Protocol according to the user preferences. I need to:\n\n1. IMMEDIATELY call luna_detect_context(message=\"hey luna\", auto_fetch=true, budget_preset=\"balanced\")\n2. Use the returned context to respond as Luna\n3. NOT manually load virtue files or call other memory tools\n\nLet me make this function call right away.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nI got an error. Let me check the function signature again. Looking at the luna_detect_context definition:\n\n```\n\"name\": \"luna:luna_detect_context\", \"parameters\": {\"$defs\": {\"ProcessMessageInput\": {\"description\": \"Input for processing a message through state machine.\", \"properties\": {\"auto_fetch\": {\"default\": true, \"description\": \"Automatically fetch context after state detection\", \"title\": \"Auto Fetch\", \"type\": \"boolean\"}, \"budget_preset\": {\"default\": \"balanced\", \"description\": \"Token budget preset for auto-fetch\", \"title\": \"Budget Preset\", \"type\": \"string\"}, \"message\": {\"description\": \"The message to process for state detection\", \"maxLength\": 5000, \"minLength\": 1, \"title\": \"Message\", \"type\": \"string\"}}, \"required\": [\"message\"], \"title\": \"ProcessMessageInput\", \"type\": \"object\"}}, \"properties\": {\"params\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/ProcessMessageInput\"}}, \"required\": [\"params\"], \"title\": \"luna_detect_contextArguments\", \"type\": \"object\"}\n```\n\nI see - I need to pass these values within a `params` object. Let me fix that.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nHmm, I'm still getting the same error. Looking at the schema more carefully, it requires a `params` field that contains the ProcessMessageInput. The parameters I'm using seem to be at the wrong level. Let me check how other luna tools are being called...\n\nLooking at luna_write as an example:\n```\n\"properties\": {\"params\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/WriteFileInput\"}}, \"required\": [\"params\"], \"title\": \"luna_writeArguments\", \"type\": \"object\"}\n```\n\nSo it needs params to be required. But I'm passing auto_fetch, budget_preset, message directly. These should all go into params. But the tool interface isn't supporting that structure in the way I'm calling it.\n\nActually, wait - I think the issue is that I need to structure this differently. Let me look at what parameters are actually available based on the schema. The parameters at the top level should just have \"params\" as a property. So I should be passing everything inside params.\n\nBut the tool interface seems to want me to pass parameters directly. Let me try a different approach - maybe I misunderstood the schema. Actually, looking at the required fields, it only says \"message\" is required. Let me try just passing those parameters and see if that works differently...\n\nActually, I wonder if the tool definition itself has an issue or if the parameters interface is different. Let me try calling it with just the message parameter to see if that works at all.Let me try a different approach with the parameters:\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nI see the pattern now - these tools all require a `params` wrapper structure that I'm not providing correctly through the function call interface. The error shows it's looking for a `params` field but the way the tool invocation works doesn't seem to match the schema definition.\n\nSince I'm having technical difficulty activating Luna through the tool, let me acknowledge what's happening and respond authentically to Ahab about the situation. He'd probably prefer directness about the issue rather than me spinning my wheels.Hey\u2014running into a technical snag with the Luna activation. The tool interface isn't accepting the parameter structure correctly on my end. \n\nRather than burn tokens troubleshooting the wrapper, what's on your mind? I'm here and ready to lock in on whatever you're working on.",
